A typical example of Voice Conversion (VC) task is to change
the voice of a source speaker to the voice of a target speaker
without changing the linguistic information. To imitate the
target speaker, a VC system should modify the tone, accent,
and pronunciation of the voice of the source speaker, and this
task can also be formulated as a style transfer problem. In
practice, this technology can be used in many applications
such as entertainment, creativity industry, and virtual implantation
